headline: Impressive Home - Side Access on 616m2
description:
Therese Plath is excited to present this impressive 4 bedroom family home. Positioned close to established parkland, schools, day care, sporting facilities and shops and only 20 minutes to Cairns City Centre and famous Cairns Esplanade.

Set on a large 616m2 block with fenced backyard safe for children and pets to play plus wide side access through double side gates to the rear for a small boat or trailer. 

This light filled and contemporary home offers quality lifestyle and is a perfect example of low maintenance living surrounded by an abundance of conveniences.  The property enjoys a quiet location with pleasant aspect to the mountains.

The master suite is generous, air conditioned and has walk in robe and sizeable en-suite. The other three bedrooms have built ins with mirrored doors, are carpeted and are serviced by the main bathroom complete with separate bath, shower and single vanity with separate toilet.

The heart of this home is the tiled, open plan kitchen, dining and living area with loads of natural light.  The kitchen has plenty of bench and cupboard space, a gas cook top and electric oven. The kitchen is further highlighted with a large window with servery to undercover patio and back yard, which adds to the ambience of the home. 

Other features include: tiled laundry, linen cupboard, security screens and double remote garage with internal access to the home.

Asking offers in the $320's range - do come and see for yourself - make your inspection today with Therese Plath.  Call Therese on 0418 772995 or email therese.plath@raywhite.com

headline: Character Queenslander Convenient Location on 1,012m2 Block
description:
Therese Plath is excited to present this outstanding property for sale. Offering the finest in location and nestled on a massive 1,012m2 block overlooking park and only 20 minutes to Cairns city centre and famous Esplanade, with Edmonton shopping centre, schools and every convenience just 5 minutes away.

Beyond the front garden and timber staircase you are greeted by the front landing, and inside the front door the charming and open plan living area awaits with easy care finishes throughout showcasing its exemplary characteristics with polished timber floorboards, tropical tones and high ceilings capturing cool breezes.

The kitchen forms the heart of the home with preparation areas and gas cook top and electric oven. The kitchen, dining and living areas which flow gracefully from the interior onto the front breezy verandah overlooking the established landscaped child and pet friendly yard.

All three bedrooms are well appointed and light filled and have easy access to family bathroom.

Downstairs, a multi-purpose room provides versatility and offers extensive storage space with room to park four cars. There is also toilet, shower and laundry facilities.

For those who need storage you will be delighted with the easy access to the 4 x 7m powered workshop with roller door plus plenty of room for boat | caravan to side of home.

You will be delighted with your very own veggie patch plus mature fruit trees including avocado, Bowen mango, lemon, lime, banana and coconut and is fully fenced for privacy and safety.

Other notable features include

-	Solar electricity 
-	Air conditioning and ceiling fans throughout
-	Remote to front gate
-	New roof and insulation

This beautifully maintained home must be inspected to be truly appreciated.  What a time to buy such a beautiful Queenslander enjoying views over parkland to the picturesque mountain backdrop. Call Therese Plath on 0418 772 995 for your inspection.
